ell.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HomoeroticSubtext" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HomoeroticSubtext">Homoerotic Subtext</a>: Teshirogi seems to take this to consideration a bit too much. There would be no yaoi fangirl who can't take any hint from how Tenma and previous Hades' vessel Alone interact; it's not exaggerating to say Alone, especially after his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeelFaceTurn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeelFaceTurn">Heel&#150;Face Turn</a>, is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FoeRomanceSubtext" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FoeRomanceSubtext">obsessed of Pegasus Tenma</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HopeSproutsEternal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HopeSproutsEternal">Hope Sprouts Eternal</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">If you're not too cynical about the ending, specially considering the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForegoneConclusion" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForegoneConclusion">Foregone Conclusion</a> that this war will happen again in the future.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HotBlooded" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HotBlooded">Hot-Blooded</a>: Tenma, just like his successor, Seiya. And still <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHero">The Hero</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumanPopsicle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumanPopsicle">Human Popsicle</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Aquarius Degel and Seraphina.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HurtingHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HurtingHero">Hurting Hero</a>: Tenma.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IAmNotLeftHanded" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.